# XPath and JsonPath in Yukthi-Transform

## Important: XPath Threading Issues

XPath expressions (`@xpath:` and `@xpathMulti:`) can cause errors in multi-threading scenarios. For better thread safety, it's recommended to disable XPath and use JsonPath expressions instead.

## Disabling XPath

To disable XPath expressions, configure the template factory:

```java
TemplateFactoryConfiguration config = new TemplateFactoryConfiguration();
config.setXpathDisabled(true);

JsonTemplateFactory factory = new JsonTemplateFactory();
factory.setTemplateFactoryConfiguration(config);
```

When XPath is disabled via [TemplateFactoryConfiguration.setXpathDisabled()](mdc:yukthi-transform/src/main/java/com/yukthitech/transform/template/TemplateFactoryConfiguration.java), any XPath expressions in templates will throw a `TransformException` at runtime.

The configuration is set via [JsonTemplateFactory.setTemplateFactoryConfiguration()](mdc:yukthi-transform/src/main/java/com/yukthitech/transform/template/JsonTemplateFactory.java).

## JsonPath as Replacement

Use JsonPath expressions as a thread-safe alternative to XPath:

- `@jpath:` - JsonPath expression (returns first match)
- `@jpathMulti:` - JsonPath expression (returns all matches)

### Examples

See [json-trans-test-data.xml](mdc:yukthi-transform/src/test/resources/json-trans-test-data.xml) for examples:

```json
{
  "jsonBookNames": "@jpathMulti: $.libraries.Justbooks.books[*].title",
  "jsonCopyCount": "@jpath: $.libraries.Justbooks.books[0].copyCount"
}
```

## Implementation Details

The XPath disabling check is implemented in [ExpressionUtils.processExpression()](mdc:yukthi-transform/src/main/java/com/yukthitech/transform/template/ExpressionUtils.java), which checks `TemplateFactoryConfiguration.isXpathDisabled()` before processing XPath expressions.

JsonPath expressions are processed using the `JsonPath` class from `com.jayway.jsonpath` library and are always available regardless of XPath configuration.

## Best Practices

1. **For multi-threaded environments**: Always disable XPath and use JsonPath
2. **Migration**: Replace `@xpath:` with `@jpath:` and `@xpathMulti:` with `@jpathMulti:` when migrating templates
